Vbank, Nigeria’s digital bank powered by VFD Microfinance Bank, has unveiled the redesigned and beautified Thompson Avenue Roundabout located in the heart of Ikoyi, Lagos. The ceremony which was witnessed by top management of the bank led by the Managing Director, Gbenga Omolokun, was said to be one of the company’s way of supporting community development. Omolokun said,‘Vbank is committed to bringing the brand closer to its customers. While many know us as a digital bank, we do need to create some offline experience that our customers can relate to. “This roundabout also serves as a strategic investment in infrastructure, and beautification
of the Community.” Also commenting on the roundabout, Olufemi Olasope, Brand Manager of Vbank, said, “Every aspect of the roundabout has been deliberately chosen to appropriately beautify the environs and communicate our brand’s message. “The greenery signifies the growth we help our customers achieve, while the walkways aim to encourage everyone to interact with us.”